  "texts": [
    "Aouad et al. (2020) and Jin et al. (2023).",
    "Despite their intuitive behaviour, CTC models are difficult to estimate in practice as one typically only knows the offer set and the customers' choice.",
    "A customers' consideration set is mostly not observable in practice and could be any subset of the full offer set or the category containing the chosen option.",
    "Hence, common choice models often assume that offer set and consideration set are equivalent, see Jagabathula et al. (2023).",
    "However, Jagabathula et al. (2023) analyse CTC models using both synthetic and real-world data sets and find that CTC models outperform classic choice models in cases when the offer set is not perfectly observable."
  ],
